                     News-Journal (Daytona Beach, Florida)

                            September 8, 2013 Sunday

Magazine: Halifax Health has nation's 49th busiest ER

SECTION: BUSINESS

LENGTH: 134  words


Ranking: Halifax has 49th busiest ER in U.S.

DAYTONA BEACH -- Halifax Health hospital system had 81,900 emergency room visits
over a one-year period, the 49th most of any hospital system in the nation,
ranking just ahead of Grady Memorial Hospital in Atlanta and just behind
Christus Spohn Hospital in Corpus Christi, Texas, according to a recently
published ranking by trade magazine Becker's Hospital Review.

Two Orlando hospital systems ranked in the top 10. Florida Hospital Orlando had
the highest number of visits in the nation at 206,800. Orlando Regional Medical
Center ranked No. 5.

At 89,000 square feet, Halifax Health, which hospitals in both Daytona Beach and
Port Orange, has the largest emergency room in the state of Florida.

-- Skyler Swisher

